# automation-529-overload-not-retried-classifier-gap -- History

## v1.2.0 (2026-07-03)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus #1793 / PR #1794 model-cap fallback session
**Verification:** verified-ci (PR #1794 merged to ProjectHephaestus main, CI green)

### What changed
- Added a THIRD transient-failure family the classifiers missed: the MODEL-SPECIFIC usage cap. The `claude`
  CLI returns a 429 envelope with "You've reached your Fable 5 limit. Run /usage-credits to continue or
  switch models with /model." — critically it carries NO reset epoch (no "resets <time>" clause), so
  `resolve_quota_reset_epoch` returns None and every wait-until-reset handler treats it as fatal. In the
  2026-07-03 automation-loop run, ~48 doomed calls failed across planner/reviewer/implementer/advise/learn
  until the run degraded to no-ops. Both failure shapes occurred: non-zero exit AND exit-0 `is_error:true`
  JSON envelope with `api_error_status: 429`.
- The key generalizable insight: the correct remediation is a MODEL SWITCH, not a wait. A 429 message that
  offers a remediation hint ("switch models") instead of a reset time is a DIFFERENT failure family from a
  quota-wait — the classifier taxonomy must distinguish "wait-until-reset" from "switch-resource"
  remediations.
- Extended `description` with trigger (8): a 429 carrying a remediation hint (switch models with /model)
  instead of a reset epoch — needs a model-switch fallback, not wait-until-reset.
- Added a "When to Use" bullet for the remediation-hint-instead-of-reset-time family and the
  wait-vs-switch taxonomy audit.
- Quick Reference: added (6) `detect_model_usage_cap(*texts)` — regex
  `reached\s+your\s+(?!session\b|usage\b)[\w .-]{1,40}?\s+limit` (negative lookahead keeps "session
  limit"/"usage limit" owned by the wait-path detectors) ORed with phrase signals "/usage-credits" and
  "switch models with /model" (three independent signals so a partial rewording still matches) — plus the
  sticky per-process `_capped_models` registry: once model M caps, the single `invoke_claude_with_session`
  chokepoint substitutes `agent_config.fallback_model()` (`HEPH_FALLBACK_MODEL` env override, default
  `claude-opus-4-8`) UP FRONT, avoiding repeated doomed ~0.5s calls (prior art in this skill: 39 doomed
  reviewer sessions/hour). Retry the SAME request once on the fallback when a cap is first detected; NO
  retry when the effective model already IS the fallback (no loop; error propagates). Envelope path scanned
  ONLY for output_format="json"; plain-text exit-0 output never scanned (agent prose can legitimately
  contain the phrases — false-positive guard).
- Added Detailed Step 9 (classify by REMEDIATION, not just by status code; fix at the ONE chokepoint, not
  per-path — reinforces this skill's core lesson); renumbered Validate to step 10.
- Added a Failed Attempts row: treating every 429 as wait-until-reset — model-specific caps have no reset
  epoch, `resolve_quota_reset_epoch` returns None and the call hard-fails; lesson: classify by remediation —
  wait vs switch.
- Results & Parameters: added the model-cap classifier, sticky cap registry, fallback-model source
  (config, never a hardcoded literal), once-only fallback retry policy, envelope-scan-scope rows, and Fix 3
  (PR #1794 / issue #1793).
- Added a third "Verified On" row for the model-cap fallback fix.
- Updated the Overview table to frame the three-instance history and bumped version 1.1.0 -> 1.2.0;
  updated `date` to 2026-07-03.

### Why
This is a MINOR bump: it adds a NEW failure family (model-specific usage cap) to the same classifier-gap
pattern the skill documents, not a rewrite. The skill previously distinguished 429-with-reset-epoch (wait)
from 529 overload (backoff-retry); this session proved there is a third family whose remediation is neither
wait nor backoff but SWITCH-RESOURCE (fall back to a different model). Capturing the wait-vs-switch
remediation taxonomy makes the skill trigger on the next "429 with a hint instead of a reset time" before
it burns dozens of doomed calls.

